
NEMAC IV is a 3D-action game with high quality graphics.

This is the freely distributable demo, version 1.006 and replaces all demos
before (including the aminet beta-demo).

Requirements:
- Amiga :-)
- OS 2.04 or better
- MC68020 or better
- 2MB continuous RAM (4MB recommended)
- 2MB space on harddisk, full version needs 8MB

Supports:
- OCS/ECS/AGA chipset
- Picasso II and CyberGraphX
- i-glasses!
- Graffiti

Several bugs have been fixed and some new features added:
- Mouse/Joystick
- More accurate controls
- CyberGraphX
- If you die, you can start with the last good "configuration"
- Some monsters leave ammunition when dying
- Strafe left & right keys
- Gamma correction

And some more internal features that make it run better ...

Installation:
All three archive parts make/unpack to the directory NEMAC_4.
Unpack all to the same directory. Then start the "InstallMe"
batchfile by double-clicking it.
It joins all three maze-parts together.
Then, please, read the ReadMe-File before you start it the
first time...